{
  "title": "Property Testing REST APIs using FastAPI with Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This guide provides an overview of how to perform property-based testing on REST APIs built with FastAPI and Python 3.12+, leveraging libraries like Hypothesis and pytest.",

  "key_points": [
    "Install necessary libraries: `pip install fastapi[test] hyphesis pytest-hypothesis`",
    "Create a conftest.py file for setup and teardown functions",
    "Write property tests using Hypothesis's `given` decorator in your test functions",
    "Use FastAPI's test client to send requests and assert the responses",
    "Ensure FastAPI router is available during tests by using @pytest.fixture",
  ],

  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "```\n\
import pytest\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI, HTTPException\nfrom hypothesis import strategies as st\nfrom hypothesis.extra.pytest import given\n\
app = FastAPI()\n\
@app.get('/example')\nasync def example():\n    return {'result': 42}\n\
def test_example():\n    @given(st.integers())\ndef test_example_with_ints(n):\n        client = app.test_client()\n        response = client.get('/example')\n        assert response.json() == {'result': n}\n\
    ```"
    },
  ],

  "version_notes": [
    "FastAPI v0.71.0 is required for `@pytest.fixture` usage",
    "Pytest-Hypothesis v5.6.3 supports FastAPI integration",
  ],

  "caveats": [
    "Ensure your test suite includes adequate coverage for various scenarios, edge cases, and error handling situations.",
    "Avoid testing slow or costly API endpoints in your property tests to maintain reasonable test execution times.",
  ]
}
